<abstract encodinganalog="520$a" label="Abstract:">Graduate, class of 1901, Smith College; Dean of Students, Smith College; and Dean of Women, Carnegie Institute of Technology.  Papers include clippings, diaries, commonplace books, geneology, photographs, passports, speeches, recipes and writings, including her autobiography, poetry, and articles.  Correspondents include her family and friends, plus the Morrow Family and William Allan Neilson.
</abstract>
